{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"cbc39d40-b327-4e96-9cfb-39947f8db958","content":"In modern MSTest (v3+), you inject `TestContext` via the constructor and use `[TestInitialize]` for async setup. Here's the recommended pattern:\n\n```csharp\n[TestClass]\npublic class MyTests\n{\n    private readonly TestContext _testContext;\n    private MyService _service;\n\n    // Synchronous init: constructor injection for TestContext\n    public MyTests(TestContext testContext)\n    {\n        _testContext = testContext;\n    }\n\n    // Asynchronous init: use [TestInitialize] returning Task\n    [TestInitialize]\n    public async Task SetupAsync()\n    {\n        _service = await MyService.CreateAsync();\n    }\n\n    [TestMethod]\n    public void ExampleTest()\n    {\n        _testContext.WriteLine(\"Running test\");\n        Assert.IsNotNull(_service);\n    }\n}\n```\n\n**Key points:**\n- **Constructor** — receives `TestContext` automatically; use for synchronous setup.\n- **`[TestInitialize] async Task`** — runs before each test; use for async setup (e.g., DB connections, HTTP clients).\n- **`[ClassInitialize]`** — available for one-time class-level setup (must be `static`).\n- Your project (MSTest 3.8.2) fully supports this pattern.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"48c77e0a-a9d2-417c-bb01-581c24cc9b0c","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user has MSTest 3.8.2 on .NET 9.0. In modern MSTest (v3+), `TestContext` can be injected via constructor. Let me provide the recommended pattern.\n\nIn MSTest v3+:\n- Constructor injection for `TestContext` is supported\n- `[TestInitialize]` can be async (returning `Task`)\n- `[ClassInitialize]` and `[ClassCleanup]` are also available\n\nLet me provide a clear, concise example.","outputTokens":445,"requestId":"6029:3665CC:25372CE:27D48AF:6A0311E8"},"id":"0d8e4ec1-33b9-4de5-9a53-c5ce052e2a0e","timestamp":"2026-05-12T11:41:39.592Z","parentId":"851c6dbf-45bb-46e1-8b9f-2af9df6ca16e"}
